<item>
            <title>[PIG-3456] Reduce threadlocal conf access in backend for each record</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3456</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Noticed few things while browsing code&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) DefaultTuple has a protected boolean isNull = false; which is never used. Removing this gives ~3-5% improvement for big jobs&lt;br/&gt;
2) Config checking with ThreadLocal conf is repeatedly done for each record. For eg: createDataBag in POCombinerPackage. But initialized only for first time in other places like POPackage, POJoinPackage, etc.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
